### Variables
@host = 192.168.1.220
@port = 80

### ============================================
### CLOCK IDENTIFICATION TEST
### ============================================
### Instructions:
### 1. Update @host to your ESP32's IP address
### 2. Start with index=0
### 3. Click "Send Request" on either hour or minute test
### 4. Note which physical clock moved and which hand
### 5. Increment index and repeat
### ============================================



### ============================================
### MOTOR TEST ENDPOINT - Direct Motor Control
### ============================================
### Use /test endpoint for direct angle positioning
### board: 0-7 (half-digit board), clock: 0-2 (clock on board)
### angle_h/angle_m: 0-359 (absolute position)
### ============================================

### Test Board 0, Clock 0 - Move hour hand to 0°
POST http://{{host}}:{{port}}/test
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

board=0&clock=0&angle_h=0

### Test Board 0, Clock 0 - Move hour hand to 90°
POST http://{{host}}:{{port}}/test
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

board=0&clock=0&angle_h=90

### Test Board 0, Clock 0 - Move hour hand to 180°
POST http://{{host}}:{{port}}/test
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

board=0&clock=0&angle_h=180

### Test Board 0, Clock 0 - Move minute hand to 0°
POST http://{{host}}:{{port}}/test
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

board=0&clock=0&angle_m=0

### Test Board 0, Clock 0 - Move minute hand to 90°
POST http://{{host}}:{{port}}/test
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

board=0&clock=0&angle_m=90

### Test Board 0, Clock 0 - Move both hands to specific positions
POST http://{{host}}:{{port}}/test
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

board=0&clock=0&angle_h=180&angle_m=270

### Test Board 0, Clock 0 - Custom speed and acceleration
POST http://{{host}}:{{port}}/test
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

board=0&clock=0&angle_h=45&angle_m=135&speed=500&accel=300


